SherpaDesk website Version #2
page instructions 
latest update Aug 22, 2014 
------------------------------

- Custom Page Header Image 
	paste the following css class into the style.css document in the site wordpress directory (change ClassName for page class name i.e. pageTitleCareers). In the wordpress wp-admin panel in the page add new section, in the custom feild labeled "sherpa-header-title" enter the ClassName entered in the css
	
		.pageTitleClassName {
		   background: url(mtt.jpg) no-repeat center center;
		   -webkit-background-size: cover;
		   -moz-background-size: cover;
		   -o-background-size: cover;
		   background-size: cover;
		   width: 100%;
		   height: 500px;
		}  


- Default Page Header Image 
	If no class is specified in the "sherpa-header-class" the default image will be applied to the page 

- Front-page 
	Is the page the serves as the index.html (homepage)